The moon is eaten by a wolf. That's what people have been saying about lunar eclipses since ancient times.

A wolf is constantly chasing the moon, and when it catches up with it, it tries to eat it and make the nights a world of complete darkness.

And when it gets dark, it tries to eat humans.

At that time, there will be many other monsters besides wolves trying to eat humans.

That's why, since ancient times, humans have tried various things to try to make the moon spit out, such as making noise or offering prayers.

However, research has now shown that this is not necessarily the reason it occurs.

Whether there is a lunar eclipse or a solar eclipse, twilight will not come to the world.

Lunar and solar eclipses are rare, but if the world were to end because of them, then the world would have ended many times over.

However, for those who are unaware of this, a lunar eclipse is still believed to be a wolf eating the moon.

The moon is a type of star, and stars are just lumps of earth that are apparently enormous in size. There's no way a wolf that big exists, and if there was, it wouldn't go out of its way to eat a human.

Even proportionally, it seems unlikely that a creature that large would be satisfied by eating a human.

There's no way a wolf that big exists.

Come to think of it, it's been almost half a month since the lunar eclipse - the day the elf's barrier was supposedly lifted.

"What do you mean, dangerous?"

If it's dangerous to walk on moonless nights, then the answer is no, you shouldn't go outside.

And yet, to stop the light from leaking outside, it really does seem like something has come out.

